## 6Jentex  Subsibiaries

As  a  truly  multinational  megacorporation,  Pentex  has  hundreds  of subsidiaries under various pseudonyms o f   different directors. For example, Harold Zettler holds controlling interest in Autumn Health Management Systems under the alias Zeldt Erohlar, a Swedish banker. The following are the star players in the Pentex lineup. These are the most profitable of the subsidiaries,  selling  cheap,  shoddy  goods  that the  consumers  want most. Most of these corporations work together for mutual gain. For example,  Young and Smith sells its Wyrm-tainted products at minimum cost to Herrick's retail chain. All in  all,  the  Pentex  subsidiaries  have a  rather incestuous  relationship.

## Arbus Lnterprises

Ardus  Enterprises claims  to  be  a  waste-management  company  that responsibly handles municipal waste,  hazardous waste and other toxic materials, such as PCBs and radioactive wastes. In fact, they are responsible  for the careless  disposal  o f  many  wastes,  often  forging  records  and  shipping  papers and switching the names and  labels of  hazardous wastes so that they  can be dumped in uncontrolled landfills or into unwatched rivers.

## Autumn Health Management Seroices

Autumn manages hospitals all over North America, and the company seeks expansion  to  Europe and Asia.  Its health  care facilities operate  at

